			"text": "Phacops is a common and widespread genus of trilobites tha lived all over the world during the Ordovician, Silurian, and Devonian periods. They were round animals with large eyes and probably fed on detritus. Many Phacops fossils are found rolled up, likely a biological defense mechanism. Some specimens of Phacops are thought to have been able to camouflage in different environments, due to irregular black spots found across the body."
